<data key="n_definition">Stage IIIA includes: (T1-T2, N1/N1c, M0); (T1, N2a, M0). T1: Tumor invades submucosa. T2: Tumor invades muscularis propria. N1: Metastasis in 1-3 regional lymph nodes. N1c: Tumor deposit(s) in the subserosa, mesentery, or nonperitonealized pericolic or perirectal tissues without regional lymph node metastasis. N2a: Metastasis in 4-6 regional lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Stage IIIA Colorectal (Colon or Rectal) Cancer|Stage IIIA Colorectal Cancer|Stage IIIA Colorectal Cancer AJCC v7</data>
