<node id="C115047">
<data key="n_label">Stage IIIA Colon Cancer AJCC v7</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Concept</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">Y</data>
<data key="n_category">Stage/Grade</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Clinical stage/course</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Neoplastic Process</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui"></data>
<data key="n_definition">Stage IIIA includes: (T1-T2, N1/N1c, M0); (T1, N2a, M0). T1: Tumor invades submucosa. T2: Tumor invades muscularis propria. N1: Metastasis in 1-3 regional lymph nodes. N1c: Tumor deposit(s) in the subserosa, mesentery, or nonperitonealized pericolic or perirectal tissues without regional lymph node metastasis. N2a: Metastasis in 4-6 regional lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Stage IIIA Colon Cancer|Stage IIIA Colon Cancer AJCC v7</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C115047</data>
