<data key="n_category">Gene/Genome</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Molecular genetics</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Amino Acid, Peptide, or Protein</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1571495</data>
<data key="n_definition">Baculoviral IAP repeat-containing protein 5 (142 aa, ~16 kDa) is encoded by the human BIRC5 gene. This protein plays a role in the regulation of both apoptosis and the cell cycle.</data>
