<data key="n_definition">Breast cancer type 1 susceptibility protein (1863 aa, ~208 kDa) is encoded by the human BRCA1 gene. This protein plays a role in both the maintenance of DNA and the mediation of ubiquitin E3 ligase activity.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">BRCA1|BRCA1 Protein|BRCA1/BRCA2-Containing Complex, Subunit 1|Breast and Ovarian Cancer Susceptibility Protein 1|Breast Cancer 1, Early Onset Protein|Breast Cancer Type 1 Susceptibility Protein|Breast-Ovarian Cancer Protein|EC 2.3.2.27|EC 6.3.2.-, Formerly|Fanconi Anemia, Complementation Group S|Protein Phosphatase 1, Regulatory Subunit 53|RING Finger Protein 53|RING-Type E3 Ubiquitin Transferase BRCA1</data>
