<node id="C12382">
<data key="n_label">Colon</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Anatomic Site</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Anatomy</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Body Part, Organ, or Organ Component</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C0009368</data>
<data key="n_definition">The longest part of the large intestine, which is a tube-like organ connected to the small intestine at one end and the anus at the other. The colon removes water and some nutrients and electrolytes from partially digested food. The remaining material, solid waste called stool, moves through the colon to the rectum and leaves the body through the anus. | The part of the large intestine measured from the cecum to the rectum consisting of ascending, transverse, descending and sigmoid portions. The purpose of the colon is to remove water from digested food prior to excretion. | The portion of the large intestine which extends from the cecum (or small intestine in animals that don't have a cecum) to the rectum.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Colon|COLON|colon|Colon structure (body structure)|Colon, NOS|large bowel|LARGE INTESTINE, COLON</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C12382</data>
</node>
<node id="C3864">
<data key="n_label">Colon Adenoma</data>
