<node id="C37930">
<data key="n_label">Constipation</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Finding/Clinical Attribute</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Phenotype/finding</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Finding</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C3551741</data>
<data key="n_definition">A condition in which stool becomes hard, dry, and difficult to pass, and bowel movements don't happen very often. Other symptoms may include painful bowel movements, and feeling bloated, uncomfortable, and sluggish. | A disorder characterized by irregular and infrequent or difficult evacuation of the bowels. | Irregular and infrequent or difficult evacuation of the bowels.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Constipation|constipation</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C37930</data>
