<data key="n_umls_cui">C0014136</data>
<data key="n_definition">A system of glands and cells that make hormones that are released directly into the blood and travel to tissues and organs all over the body. The endocrine system controls growth, sexual development, sleep, hunger, and the way the body uses food. | Anatomical system that consists of the glands and parts of glands that produce endocrine secretions and help to integrate and control bodily metabolic activity. | The body system that comprises the organs and glands that produce hormones that are secreted into the blood and control physiological functions that include reproduction, growth and development, metabolism, and stress responses.</data>
