<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Treatment Regimen</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Therapy</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Therapeutic or Preventive Procedure</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1881116</data>
<data key="n_definition">A regimen consisting of irinotecan, fluorouracil, leucovorin and bevacizumab used for the treatment of advanced stage colorectal cancer.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">IFL and Bevacizumab|IFL and Bevacizumab-adcd|IFL and Bevacizumab-awwb|IFL and Bevacizumab-aybi|IFL and Bevacizumab-bvzr|IFL and Bevacizumab-equi|IFL and Bevacizumab-maly|IFL and Bevacizumab-onbe|IFL and Bevacizumab-tnjn|IFL-Avastin Regimen|IFL-Bevacizumab Regimen|Irinotecan-Fluorouracil-Leucovorin-Bevacizumab Regimen|Irinotecan/Fluorouracil/Leucovorin/Bevacizumab Regimen</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C63607</data>
</node>
<node id="C63717">
<data key="n_label">IFL-Douillard Regimen</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Treatment Regimen</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Therapy</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Therapeutic or Preventive Procedure</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1881117</data>
<data key="n_definition">A regimen consisting of irinotecan, infusional fluorouracil and leucovorin used for the treatment of advanced stage colorectal cancer. This regimen differs from the FOLFIRI regimen with regards to the dose of fluorouracil administered.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Douillard Regimen|IFL-Douillard Regimen|Irinotecan-Fluorouracil-Leucovorin Douillard Regimen</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C63717</data>
</node>
<node id="C64191">
<data key="n_label">IFL-FOLFIRI Regimen</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Treatment Regimen</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Therapy</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Therapeutic or Preventive Procedure</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1881118</data>
<data key="n_definition">A regimen consisting of irinotecan, infusional fluorouracil and leucovorin used for the treatment of advanced stage colorectal cancer. This regimen differs from the Douillard regimen with regards to the dose of fluorouracil administered.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">IFL-FOLFIRI Regimen|Irinotecan-Fluorouracil-Leucovorin FOLFIRI Regimen</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C64191</data>
</node>
<node id="C77205">
<data key="n_label">ING2 Gene</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Gene/Genome</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Molecular genetics</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Gene or Genome</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1416437</data>
<data key="n_definition">This gene plays a role in the modulation of both protein acetylation and apoptosis.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">ING2|ING2 Gene|Inhibitor of Growth Family, Member 2 Gene</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C77205</data>
</node>
<node id="C77206">
<data key="n_label">ING2 wt Allele</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Gene/Genome</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Molecular genetics</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Gene or Genome</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C2697655</data>
<data key="n_definition">Human ING2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 4q35.1 and is approximately 6 kb in length. This allele, which encodes inhibitor of growth protein 2, is involved in the regulation of apoptosis and protein acetylation. Aberrant expression of the gene is associated with colon tumors.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">ING1L|ING2 wt Allele|Inhibitor of Growth Family, Member 1-Like Gene|Inhibitor of Growth Family, Member 2 wt Allele|p33ING2</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C77206</data>
</node>
<node id="C153483">
<data key="n_label">IROX-Bevacizumab Regimen</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Treatment Regimen</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Therapy</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Therapeutic or Preventive Procedure</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1541404</data>
<data key="n_definition">A regimen consisting of bevacizumab, irinotecan and oxaliplatin that can be used for the treatment of appendiceal adenocarcinoma and colorectal cancer.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Bevacizumab-Irinotecan-Oxaliplatin Regimen|Bevacizumab/Irinotecan/Oxaliplatin Regimen|IROX (Irinotecan/Oxaliplatin) + Bevacizumab|IROX + Bevacizumab|IROX + Bevacizumab Regimen|IROX Plus Bevacizumab|IROX-Bevacizumab Regimen|IROX/Bev|Oxaliplatin/Irinotecan + Bevacizumab</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C153483</data>
</node>
<node id="C36118">
<data key="n_label">In Situ Lesion</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Finding/Clinical Attribute</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Phenotype/finding</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Finding</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1334167</data>
<data key="n_definition">A morphologic finding that usually refers either to intraepithelial dysplastic and architectural changes that involve the entire thickness of the epithelium without invasion of the basement membrane (carcinoma in situ) or proliferation of atypical melanocytes in the dermal-epidermal junction without infiltration of the papillary or reticular dermis (lentigo maligna).</data>
<data key="n_aliases">In Situ Lesion|In Situ Neoplasm</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C36118</data>
</node>
<node id="C36683">
<data key="n_label">Inactivating APC Gene Mutation</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Molecular Abnormality</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Molecular genetics</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Cell or Molecular Dysfunction</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1515857</data>
<data key="n_definition">A change in the nucleotide sequence of the APC gene that either inhibits expression or results in the translation of an inactive adenomatosis polyposis coli protein.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">APC Gene Inactivation|APC Inactivating Gene Mutation|APC Inactivating Mutation|APC Loss of Function Gene Mutation|APC Loss of Function Mutation|APC Tumor-Suppressor Gene Inactivation|Inactivating Adenomatosis Polyposis Gene Mutation|Inactivating APC Gene Mutation|Inactivating APC Mutation|Inactivating APC, WNT Signaling Pathway Regulator Gene Mutation|Inactivating BTPS2 Gene Mutation|Inactivating FAP Gene Mutation|Inactivating FPC Gene Mutation|Inactivating PPP1R46 Gene Mutation</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C36683</data>
</node>
<node id="C3138">
<data key="n_label">Inflammatory Bowel Disease</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Associated Disease/Neoplasm</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Associated conditions</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Disease or Syndrome</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C4227559</data>
<data key="n_definition">A general term that refers to the inflammation of the colon and rectum. Inflammatory bowel disease includes ulcerative colitis and Crohn's disease. | A spectrum of small and large bowel inflammatory diseases of unknown etiology. It includes Crohn's disease, ulcerative colitis, and colitis of indeterminate type. | Chronic inflammatory process affecting the gastrointestinal tract; primarily ulcerative colitis and Crohn's disease.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Autoimmune Bowel Disorder|IBD|Inflammatory Bowel Disease|inflammatory bowel disease</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C3138</data>
</node>
<node id="C136257">
<data key="n_label">Infusional Fluorouracil/Leucovorin/Bevacizumab Regimen</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Treatment Regimen</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Therapy</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Therapeutic or Preventive Procedure</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui"></data>
<data key="n_definition">A regimen consisting of infusional fluorouracil, leucovorin and bevacizumab that is used for the treatment of colorectal cancer, and ampullary, appendiceal and small bowel adenocarcinoma.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Infusional 5-FU/LV Plus Bevacizumab|Infusional Fluorouracil-Leucovorin-Bevacizumab Regimen|Infusional Fluorouracil/Leucovorin Plus Avastin|Infusional Fluorouracil/leucovorin Plus Bevacizumab|Infusional Fluorouracil/Leucovorin/Avastin|Infusional Fluorouracil/Leucovorin/Bevacizumab Regimen</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C136257</data>
</node>
<node id="C77207">
<data key="n_label">Inhibitor of Growth Protein 2</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Gene/Genome</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Molecular genetics</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Amino Acid, Peptide, or Protein</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1432406</data>
<data key="n_definition">Inhibitor of growth protein 2 (280 aa, ~33 kDa) is encoded by the human ING2 gene. This protein plays a role in apoptosis through the modulation of the acetylation of tumor protein 53.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">ING1Lp|Inhibitor of Growth 1-Like Protein|Inhibitor of Growth Protein 2|p32|p33ING2</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C77207</data>
</node>
<node id="C155862">
<data key="n_label">Intermediate Grade Neuroendocrine Lesion</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Finding/Clinical Attribute</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Phenotype/finding</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Finding</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui"></data>
<data key="n_definition">A neoplastic lesion with neuroendocrine differentiation and histological features of intermediate grade.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Intermediate Grade Neuroendocrine Lesion</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C155862</data>
</node>
<node id="C226752">
<data key="n_label">Intestinal Low Grade Tubuloglandular Adenocarcinoma</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Associated Disease/Neoplasm</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Associated conditions</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Neoplastic Process</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui"></data>
<data key="n_definition">An uncommon, low-grade adenocarcinoma that arises from the intestine and is characterized by the presence of extremely well differentiated malignant small or medium sized glands with round or tubular shape and absence of desmoplastic stroma formation. It typically occurs in patients with long-standing inflammatory bowel disease and approximately 10% of inflammatory bowel disease-associated intestinal carcinomas are low-grade tubuloglandular adenocarcinomas.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Intestinal LGTGA|Intestinal Low Grade Tubuloglandular Adenocarcinoma|Intestinal Low-Grade Tubuloglandular Adenocarcinoma</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C226752</data>
</node>
<node id="C8360">
<data key="n_label">Intestinal Metaplasia</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Finding/Clinical Attribute</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Phenotype/finding</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Finding</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C0334037</data>
<data key="n_definition">A morphologic finding indicating the replacement of epithelial tissue outside the intestines by intestinal-type epithelium.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Intestinal Metaplasia|Intestinal metaplasia</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C8360</data>
</node>
<node id="C96063">
<data key="n_label">Intestinal Neuroendocrine Carcinoma</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Associated Disease/Neoplasm</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Associated conditions</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Neoplastic Process</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C3272530</data>
<data key="n_definition">An aggressive high-grade carcinoma with neuroendocrine differentiation that arises from the small or large intestine. It is composed of malignant small or large cells. The mitotic count is more than 20 per 2 mm2 and/or the Ki-67 index is more than 20%.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Intestinal High Grade Neuroendocrine Carcinoma|Intestinal NEC|Intestinal Neuroendocrine Carcinoma|Intestinal Poorly Differentiated Endocrine Carcinoma</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C96063</data>
</node>
<node id="C12736">
<data key="n_label">Intestine</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Anatomic Site</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Anatomy</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Body Part, Organ, or Organ Component</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C0021853</data>
<data key="n_definition">Segment of the alimentary canal extending from the stomach to the anus and, in humans and other mammals, consists of two segments, the small intestine and the large intestine. | The long, tube-shaped organ in the abdomen that completes the process of digestion. The intestine has two parts, the small intestine and the large intestine. | The portion of the gastrointestinal tract between the stomach and the anus. It includes the small intestine and large intestine. | The portion of the gastrointestinal tract that includes the small and large intestines.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Bowel|bowel|Intestinal structure (body structure)|Intestinal tract, NOS|Intestine|INTESTINE|intestine|Intestines</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C12736</data>
</node>
<node id="C95397">
<data key="n_label">Intramucosal Adenocarcinoma</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Associated Disease/Neoplasm</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Associated conditions</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Neoplastic Process</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C2987120</data>
<data key="n_definition">A neoplastic lesion that shows morphologic evidence of invasion into the lamina propria or muscularis mucosa. There is no evidence of invasion into the submucosa. Evidence of invasion may refer to stromal invasion by single cells or clusters of cells, presence of atypical and complex glandular architectural patterns beyond those that are present in normal mucosa, desmoplasia, and/or vascular invasion.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Intramucosal Adenocarcinoma</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C95397</data>
</node>
<node id="C60663">
<data key="n_label">Intramucosal Lesion</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Finding/Clinical Attribute</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Phenotype/finding</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Finding</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1881243</data>
<data key="n_definition">A pathologic process that is confined to the mucosa.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Intramucosal Lesion</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C60663</data>
</node>
<node id="C9480">
<data key="n_label">Invasive Carcinoma</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Associated Disease/Neoplasm</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Associated conditions</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Neoplastic Process</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1334274</data>
<data key="n_definition">A carcinoma that is not confined to the epithelium, and has spread to the surrounding stroma.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Invasive Carcinoma</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C9480</data>
</node>
<node id="C36117">
<data key="n_label">Invasive Lesion</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Finding/Clinical Attribute</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Phenotype/finding</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Finding</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1334278</data>
<data key="n_definition">A malignant cellular population that has increased in size and infiltrates the surrounding tissues.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Invasive|Invasive Lesion</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C36117</data>
</node>
<node id="C153481">
<data key="n_label">Irinotecan/Panitumumab Regimen</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Treatment Regimen</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Therapy</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Therapeutic or Preventive Procedure</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui"></data>
<data key="n_definition">A regimen consisting of irinotecan and panitumumab that can be used for the treatment of colorectal cancer and appendiceal cancer.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Irinotecan + Panitumumab Regimen|Irinotecan-Panitumumab|Irinotecan-Panitumumab Regimen|Irinotecan/Panitumumab|Irinotecan/Panitumumab Regimen|Panitumumab/Irinotecan</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C153481</data>
</node>
<node id="C153482">
<data key="n_label">Irinotecan/Panitumumab/Vemurafenib Regimen</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Treatment Regimen</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Therapy</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Therapeutic or Preventive Procedure</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui"></data>
<data key="n_definition">A regimen consisting of irinotecan, panitumumab and vemurafenib that can be used for the treatment of colon cancer.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Irinotecan + Panitumumab + Vemurafenib|Irinotecan + Panitumumab + Vemurafenib Regimen|Irinotecan + Panitumumab Regimen|Irinotecan-Panitumumab-Vemurafenib|Irinotecan-Panitumumab-Vemurafenib Regimen|Irinotecan/Panitumumab/Vemurafenib|Irinotecan/Panitumumab/Vemurafenib Regimen</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C153482</data>
</node>
<node id="C136260">
<data key="n_label">Irinotecan/Ramucirumab Regimen</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Treatment Regimen</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Therapy</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Therapeutic or Preventive Procedure</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui"></data>
<data key="n_definition">A regimen consisting of irinotecan and ramucirumab that is used for the treatment of appendiceal adenocarcinoma, colon, esophageal and esophagogastric junction, gastric and rectal cancers.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Irinotecan-Cyramza Regimen|Irinotecan-Ramucirumab|Irinotecan-Ramucirumab Regimen|Irinotecan/Cyramza Regimen|Irinotecan/Ramucirumab|Irinotecan/Ramucirumab Regimen</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C136260</data>
</node>
<node id="C136259">
<data key="n_label">Irinotecan/Ziv-aflibercept Regimen</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Treatment Regimen</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Therapy</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Therapeutic or Preventive Procedure</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui"></data>
<data key="n_definition">A regimen consisting of irinotecan and ziv-aflibercept that is used for the treatment of appendiceal adenocarcinoma and colorectal cancer.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Irinotecan-Zaltrap Regimen|Irinotecan-Ziv-aflibercept|Irinotecan-Ziv-aflibercept Regimen|Irinotecan/Zaltrap Regimen|Irinotecan/Ziv-aflibercept|Irinotecan/Ziv-aflibercept Regimen</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C136259</data>
</node>
<node id="C3143">
<data key="n_label">Jaundice</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Finding/Clinical Attribute</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Phenotype/finding</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Finding</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C3549846</data>
<data key="n_definition">A condition in which the skin and the whites of the eyes become yellow, urine darkens, and the color of stool becomes lighter than normal. Jaundice occurs when the liver is not working properly or when a bile duct is blocked. | Yellow pigmentation of the skin, mucous membranes, and the eyes due to hyperbilirubinemia. | Yellow pigmentation of the skin, mucous membranes, and the eyes due to hyperbilirubinemia. Causes include liver disease, biliary tract obstruction, and hemolysis. | Yellowish pigmentation of the skin, mucous membranes, and the eyes.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Jaundice|jaundice</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C3143</data>
</node>
<node id="C7754">
<data key="n_label">Juvenile Polyposis Syndrome</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Associated Disease/Neoplasm</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Associated conditions</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Neoplastic Process</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C0345893</data>
<data key="n_definition">An autosomal dominant hereditary neoplastic syndrome. Mutations in the SMAD4 or BMPR1A genes have been identified in some patients. It is characterized by the presence of multiple juvenile polyps in the gastrointestinal tract.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Juvenile Multiple Polyps Syndrome|Juvenile Polyposis|Juvenile Polyposis Coli|Juvenile Polyposis Syndrome</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C7754</data>
</node>
<node id="C25785">
<data key="n_label">KRAS Gene</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Gene/Genome</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Molecular genetics</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Gene or Genome</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1537502</data>
<data key="n_definition">A gene that may cause cancer when it is mutated (changed). The Kras gene makes the KRAS protein, which is involved in cell signaling pathways, cell growth, and apoptosis (cell death). Agents that block the activity of the mutated Kras gene or its protein may stop the growth of cancer. | This gene is involved in signal transduction and apoptosis.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">K-ras gene|KRAS|KRAS Gene|Kras gene|KRas Proto-Oncogene, GTPase Gene</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C25785</data>
</node>
<node id="C36665">
<data key="n_label">KRAS Gene Amplification</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Molecular Abnormality</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Molecular genetics</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Cell or Molecular Dysfunction</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1517648</data>
<data key="n_definition">A molecular genetic abnormality indicating the presence of multiple copies of the KRAS gene.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">c-K-ras Gene Amplification|KRAS Amplification|KRAS Gene Amplification|KRAS-2 Gene Amplification|KRAS2 Gene Amplification|v-Ki-ras2 Kirsten Rat Sarcoma Viral Oncogene Homolog Gene Amplification</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C36665</data>
</node>
<node id="C52546">
<data key="n_label">KRAS wt Allele</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Gene/Genome</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Molecular genetics</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Gene or Genome</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1705982</data>
<data key="n_definition">Human KRAS wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 12p12.1 and is approximately 45 kb in length. This allele, which encodes GTPase KRas protein, plays a role in the modulation of both cellular proliferation and differentiation. Mutations in the gene are associated with juvenile myelomonocytic leukemia, Noonan syndrome 3 and cardiofaciocutaneous syndrome.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">C-K-RAS|C-K-Ras Oncogene|Cellular c-Ki-Ras2 Proto-Oncogene|CFC2|K-Ras 2A|K-RAS2A|K-RAS2B|K-RAS4A|K-RAS4B|KI-RAS|Kirsten Rat Sarcoma Viral Oncogene Homolog Gene|KRas Proto-Oncogene, GTPase wt Allele|KRAS wt Allele|KRAS1|KRAS2|NS|NS3|PR310|RALD|RASK2|v-Ki-RAS2 Kirsten Rat Sarcoma 2 Viral Oncogene Homolog Gene|v-Ki-Ras2 Kirsten Rat Sarcoma Viral Oncogene Homolog Gene</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C52546</data>
</node>
