<data key="n_category">Gene/Genome</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Molecular genetics</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Gene or Genome</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1705342</data>
<data key="n_definition">Human PTPN12 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 7q11.23 and is approximately 103 kb in length. This allele, which encodes tyrosine-protein phosphatase non-receptor type 12 protein, plays a role in the dephosphorylation of protein-tyrosine phosphates. Defects in the PTPN12 gene are associated with colon cancer.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Protein Tyrosine Phosphatase, Non-Receptor Type 12 wt Allele|PTP-PEST|PTPG1|PTPN12 wt Allele</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C49520</data>
