<node id="C222055">
<data key="n_label">Polymerase Proofreading-Associated Polyposis</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Associated Disease/Neoplasm</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Associated conditions</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Disease or Syndrome</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui"></data>
<data key="n_definition">An autosomal dominant inherited neoplastic syndrome caused by germline mutations in the DNA polymerase proofreading genes POLE or POLD1. It is characterized by the presence of multiple colorectal adenomatous polyps and is associated with an increased risk of developing colorectal cancer, endometrial cancer, and less often gastric cancer, duodenal cancer, pancreatic cancer, breast cancer, and ovarian cancer.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Polymerase Proofreading-Associated Polyposis|PPAP</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C222055</data>
</node>
<node id="C3340">
<data key="n_label">Polyp</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Associated Disease/Neoplasm</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Associated conditions</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Disease or Syndrome</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C0032584</data>
<data key="n_definition">A growth that protrudes from a mucous membrane. | A usually exophytic mass attached to the underlying tissue by a broad base or a thin stalk. Polyps can be neoplastic or non-neoplastic. Neoplastic polyps usually represent proliferations of the epithelium, and are commonly seen in the gastrointestinal tract. Polyps of the gastrointestinal tract are often called adenomas, are associated with dysplasia, and may eventually transform into carcinomas. Non-neoplastic polyps may be inflammatory, degenerative, or the result of malformations.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Polyp|polyp</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C3340</data>
</node>
<node id="C95744">
