<data key="n_research_axis">Molecular genetics</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Gene or Genome</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1709800</data>
<data key="n_definition">Human RAD54B wild-type allele is located within 8q21.3-q22 and is approximately 103 kb in length. This allele, which encodes DNA repair and recombination protein RAD54B, plays a role in both mitotic recombination and DNA repair. Certain allelic variants of the RAD54B gene are associated with several types of cancer such as colon cancer and primary lymphoma.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">RAD54 Homolog B (S. cerevisiae) Gene|RAD54 Homolog B wt Allele|RAD54, S. cerevisiae, Homolog of, B Gene|RAD54B wt Allele|RDH54</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C49408</data>
</node>
