<data key="n_umls_cui">C0205697</data>
<data key="n_definition">A malignant epithelial neoplasm characterized by the presence of spindle cells and anaplastic morphologic features. Giant cells and a sarcomatous component may also be present. | A malignant epithelial neoplasm characterized by the presence of spindle cells. | A type of cancer that begins in the skin or in tissues that line or cover internal organs and that contains long spindle-shaped cells.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">CARCINOMA, SPINDLE CELL, MALIGNANT|Pseudosarcomatous Carcinoma|Pseudosarcomatous carcinoma|Sarcomatoid Carcinoma|Sarcomatoid carcinoma|sarcomatoid carcinoma|Spindle Cell Carcinoma</data>
