<data key="n_definition">A histopathologic finding characterized by the presence of malignant cells of connective tissue origin in a tumor sample. Examples of connective tissue cells that can undergo malignant transformation include smooth and skeletal muscle cells, adipose tissue cells, osteocytes, and chondrocytes.</data>
