<node id="C17359">
<data key="n_label">TP53 Gene</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Gene/Genome</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Molecular genetics</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Gene or Genome</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C0079419</data>
<data key="n_definition">This gene plays a critical role in cell cycle regulation and has tumor suppressor activity.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">P53|TP53|TP53 Gene|Tumor Protein P53 (Li-Fraumeni Syndrome) Gene</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C17359</data>
</node>
<node id="C36329">
<data key="n_label">TP53 Gene Inactivation</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Molecular Abnormality</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Molecular genetics</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Cell or Molecular Dysfunction</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1515171</data>
<data key="n_definition">A mutation in the TP53 gene that either inhibits the expression of or results in the translation of an inactive cellular tumor antigen p53 protein.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Inactivating TP53 Gene Mutation|Inactivation of p53 Tumor-Suppressor Gene|LFS1 Gene Inactivation|Li-Fraumeni Syndrome Gene Inactivation|P53 Gene Inactivation|P53 Loss of Function Gene Mutation|P53 Tumor-Suppressor Gene Inactivation|TP53 Gene Inactivation|TP53 Loss of Function Gene Mutation|TP53 Tumor-Suppressor Gene Inactivation|TRP53 Gene Inactivation|Tumor Protein p53 Gene Inactivation</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C36329</data>
</node>
<node id="C52271">
<data key="n_label">TP53 wt Allele</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Gene/Genome</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Molecular genetics</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Gene or Genome</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C1705526</data>
<data key="n_definition">A tumor suppressor gene that normally inhibits the growth of tumors. This gene is altered in many types of cancer. | Human TP53 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17p13.1 and is approximately 19 kb in length. This allele, which encodes cellular tumor antigen p53 protein, plays a role in cell cycle regulation during the G0/G1transition. Alterations of the TP53 gene occur as both somatic and germline mutations in human malignancies in select cancer-prone families with Li-Fraumeni syndrome.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">BCC7|FLJ92943|LFS1|P53|p53|p53 gene|p53 wild type|TP53|TP53 wt Allele|TRP53|Tumor Protein P53 (Li-Fraumeni Syndrome) wt Allele|Tumor Protein p53 Gene</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C52271</data>
</node>
<node id="C97240">
<data key="n_label">TP53*1 Allele</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Gene/Genome</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Molecular genetics</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Gene or Genome</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C3273300</data>
<data key="n_definition">Human TP53*1 allele is located in the vicinity of 17p13.1 and is approximately 19 kb in length. This allele, which encodes cellular tumor antigen p53*1 protein, is involved in apoptosis and tumor suppression. This variant exhibits a coding change from a proline at amino acid 72 to an arginine, which may affect the activity and stability of the encoded protein.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">TP53 c.215C&gt;G|TP53 Codon 72 Polymorphism|TP53 p.Pro72Arg|TP53 P72R|TP53*1 Allele|Tumor Protein p53*1 Allele</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C97240</data>
</node>
<node id="C60661">
<data key="n_label">Tenesmus</data>
<data key="n_node_kind">Entity</data>
<data key="n_in_colorectal_tree">N</data>
<data key="n_category">Finding/Clinical Attribute</data>
<data key="n_research_axis">Phenotype/finding</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Finding</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui">C0232726</data>
<data key="n_definition">Painful spasm of the anal sphincter along with an urgent desire to defecate without the significant production of feces; associated with irritable bowel syndrome.</data>
<data key="n_aliases">Tenesmus</data>
<data key="n_nci_url">https://ncit.nci.nih.gov/ncitbrowser/ConceptReport.jsp?dictionary=NCI_Thesaurus&amp;ns=ncit&amp;code=C60661</data>
</node>
<node id="C12905">
<data key="n_label">Thoracic Cavity</data>
