<data key="n_research_axis">Therapy</data>
<data key="n_semantic_types">Therapeutic or Preventive Procedure</data>
<data key="n_umls_cui"></data>
<data key="n_definition">A regimen consisting of a modified version of FOLFOX, which contains leucovorin, infusional fluorouracil and oxaliplatin, used for the treatment of appendiceal and small bowel adenocarcinomas, and colorectal cancer.</data>
